--- !u!114 &260321708
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 260321706}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9541d86e2fd84c1d9990edf0852d74ab, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Throughout your rehabilitation journey, you or your therapist might want
    to make the therapy more or less challenging. To do so, you can decide on the
    amount of guidance you receive. Guidance means seeing the target posture and
    no guidance means having no target posture to help guide your movement (see images
    below). 33% guidance (LOW) means seeing the target posture every third trial.
    50% guidance (MEDIUM) means seeing the target posture every other trial. 100%
    guidance (HIGH) means seeing the target posture every trial. The guidance is
    related to the grasp type. For example, if you choose 50%, you will see the target
    posture the first time you reach for a block but not the second time. If you
    are early on in therapy, it is recommended that you choose 100%, but should consult
    with your therapist.   \r\n\r\nWhat frequency would you like? Say \u201Clow guidance\u201D,
    \u201Cmedium guidance\u201D or \u201Chigh guidance\u201D. "
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a84f857bec7e7345843ae29404c57ce, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: 21202819797275496, guid: 6a84f857bec7e7345843ae29404c57ce, type: 2}
