  m_text: To display the target grasp, say the specific object that you want to grasp.
    For example, if you want to grasp a block, say "block". Next, a target grasp
    will appear in two different representations in the top right corner of the screen.
    One representation is a collection of yellow lines representing bone and joint
    location (similar to your hand tracking). The other representation is a grey
    depiction of a hand in the matching posture. See the example on the right. If
    you say the wrong object by accident, please say "redo trial" and try again.
